##Volunteer Ryan Cheng: What they lack is the last care on earth

Lifeweek

Features an introduction to a magazine and the life he advocates.

The epidemic swept the city into the wheel, most people are passive, but some people, take the initiative to join, in the city, chivalrous spirit, do something for Wuhan People.

Reporter | BOJING (from Wuhan)
Photography | Huang Yu

Reporter | BOJING (from Wuhan)

Photography | Huang Yu

At night

"everything. We have everything. "

The volunteer sent me a location, didn't say when I'd get it, just that I had all the protection I needed. I hurried out the door, thinking that the sooner the better. It was 8 pm and the photographer, Lao Huang, was out interviewing with another colleague when he got my message. The car had just arrived at the hotel, and he came back just in time. Just hear me out. Huang didn't even go upstairs. I grabbed a mask, put it on, thought about it, stuffed two more layers into my bag, and went downstairs to meet him.

Located at a Bistro, between Wuchang District Friendship Boulevard and Peace Boulevard, across the river from our hotel, just across the second Yangtze River Bridge, 20 minutes to reach.

I'll sync up with Huang in the car. I know what I know. The truth is, I don't know much, except that we went to the tavern and met up with a few volunteers. After arriving at the Bistro, dress up here with protective gear and go to the home of the new pneumonia patient together. The contact was Ryan Cheng, one of the volunteers who had been responding to online requests for help. On Weibo, "pneumonia patients ask for help in Super Talk" is highly exposed. Many desperate patients have no choice but to send symptoms and other conditions to this "super talk" . They are reposted in large numbers, also often in the form of screenshots spread in Wechat Circle of friends. The names and numbers of people asking for help are spread across the Internet.

On the night of Feb. 7, a mother-in-law in her late 80s died at home. Volunteers posted on their friends' circle, "grandma has no pulse and doesn't need a bed. ". Ryan Cheng and two other volunteers went to the funeral home in the evening.

Entering the tavern, the atmosphere was tense. It was my fourth day in Wuhan. I've been to the quarantine hotel in the morning to visit my grandfather with Zhou Yang, a young man who has been treating his family, and I've been to the out patient lobby of the God bless hospital in the middle of the day, but it's not as tense as this. I felt my heart beat faster, for one thing, because Ryan Cheng was talking so fast, telling us what to wear, and for another, answering the phone and texting as if he had a million things to do at once. The second was that the tavern was dimly lit, with no clear view, and the bar was dark inside and lighted outside, but barely enough to see. We walked along the bar to the deepest part of the tavern, where we dressed and asked questions, like underground party couriers; Scattered on the ground a few boxes of protective materials, there are masks on the table and so on a should be equipped, as previously said, "everything has. ". Three, because, just 10 kilometers away, the family of the deceased is waiting for us. The family has a son Lu Guoxiu, more than 50 years old, new pneumonia confirmed patients, granddaughter Lu Haiyue, Early Twenties, is at a loss. The journey is imminent.

Two cars, them in front, me and old Huang close behind. Parked on a street near South Central Road in Wuchang District, and entered on foot.

Thick night, the same dim street lights in the community. There was a crowd of people in front of the community service center, some in security uniforms, some armed men like us, and two police station suvs parked in front of the neighborhood. A few minutes later, the two cars took the lead, the lane was narrow, and the turnaround was laborious. Most of the people present were attracted by them and saw them off. The window of one of the cars dropped slowly, and a voice pointed in Ryan Cheng's direction and said, "that's very kind of you, " as Ryan Cheng tactfully responded, "it's the right thing to do. ". Outside the crowd, there was a young girl in Pink Fleece Pajamas, a black down jacket, a simple mask over her face, hard to see, but with a force in her eyes. As soon as I spoke to her, I moved two steps to the right. "better stay away from me. " "I haven't been tested, but I'm definitely infected. ". From about three meters away, we had a few words. I didn't dare ask. She had an obvious cry in her voice. It was her grandmother who had just died.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Ryan Cheng asked community workers what procedures would be followed after a new pneumonia patient died at home. That, first, call the CDC, they sent someone to sterilize; Second, a death certificate; third, the funeral home to pick up the body.

As the crowd dispersed, three volunteers, including Ryan Cheng, and myself, Huang, and Ms. Lu, moved to the building where Ms. Lu's family lived. It was 9:30 at night.

"crying solves nothing, " Ms. Lu said on Feb. 7. "tears are the least valuable thing. ".

Go to the third floor. The door was open, and Luhaiyue, three volunteers and Lao Huang entered in turn. I stayed behind. By the time I got to the door, I could no longer enter the living room at Harvard, there's not much room to turn around. I stood at the door and looked around. It was a two-room, one-hall, without a vestibule, with the door facing the kitchen, which was closed. In his right hand came two bedroom doors, one closed, the other open, and out came Lu Guoxiu, who was putting on his coat and moving his hands, but he was silent, just standing there, not making small talk. Inside the closed door lay Lu Haiyue's grandmother, who had died a few hours earlier.

A few minutes later, I went inside, and the dog barking, which had only just begun to sound vaguely outside the door, became loud and clear. It was right in front of me. It must have been shut up in the kitchen. Luhaiyue tidied up both pockets and finally asked, "what about the dog? " Ryan Cheng replied, "what time is it and you can manage the dog. "

Volunteers with a large watering can, to the sea on Grandma's room wantonly disinfection. The CDC told Ryan Cheng on the phone that they would come, but that they would have to wait, with seven more waiting in line. A man in his 30s at the CDC later confirmed to me that they would have needed the next day to come in. Seven families, each of them on average to spend two hours, the Lu turn, at least the next day at noon.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
But even if the night had been sterilized, Lu Haiyue and her father could not have stayed in the house overnight. First of all, from small to big, Lu Haiyue is with grandma sleep a room, a bed, although is head to foot, is also intimate. Now the deceased grandmother had to stay in the house, with only one room left, a father and daughter, with nowhere to go.

The question before Ryan Cheng is what to do with them.

The ideal, of course, is for the community to step in and arrange for them to be quarantined. Lu Guoxiu early diagnosis, nucleic acid test was positive, had a high fever of 39.8 degrees Celsius, home isolation a few days later, fever, symptoms reduced, if put a number of days later, "should be collected" policy, can be admitted to the shelter hospital. And Lu Haiyue, as close contacts, should also be received by the isolation hotel, starting with nucleic acid testing, step by step forward. But right now, the situation is dire, and the community has no intention of stepping in.

I remembered that during the day, Huang and I had gone to a segregated hotel called Sunny Day, where we had followed Zhou Yang, a young man, to visit his grandfather. Desperate Times call for desperate measures. I say we take our chances on a sunny day. However, first, there is no street issued a certificate, and second, they are not in the same jurisdiction, can be accepted unlikely.

Ryan Cheng, who had found the nearest hotel on a map and was within ten minutes of it, boarded us in the other car. Huang was driving, I was in the passenger seat, and Ryan Cheng was in the back seat, "It's only $200 a night, and they've just lost their loved ones, and they're looking for another hotel, " Ryan Cheng said, explaining that one had just lost his grandmother, the other his mother, their destination for the night, if it was a Shabby Inn, he could not bear it.

Two cars in the darkness of Wuhan, this time is our car in front, the other car behind, but we do not know where to go. As Huang drove, hesitating that there was no definite destination, I looked back at Ryan Cheng and waited for him to make up his mind. After a few minutes of hesitation, he made a call from the back seat, his tone still urgent: "Do you have a room for tonight" , "a suite will do" , "I have money, will 10,000 yuan be enough? "? He hung up the phone, made an emergency U-TURN, and found a hotel for his father and daughter that he thought was decent. To my surprise, there are open hotels in this period.

Finding his footing, Ryan Cheng relaxed and began to tell us what had happened that afternoon.

In the evening

What happened on the evening of February 7th was the death of a very sick old man. These scenes are not easily narrated, nor easily restored, but Lu Haiyue can not forget them. On the third day, she checked into the isolation hotel, and a week later, she was able to move back into the shelter, where no matter where she went, she couldn't sleep well at night, thinking of grandma and the dog. She and her father were with her, and Ryan Cheng, who was half her father and half her daughter, saw her for the last time on video.

The luhaiyue family is the Second Family Ryan Cheng has helped since he began volunteering. Ryan Cheng went to Lu's house for the first time, bringing food such as meat and instant noodles, as well as face masks and electric blankets. Lu Haiyue went to the intersection to meet him, saw him carrying two large bags of things, under the rain, did not have an umbrella. Lu Haiyue thought, at this time, even their relatives are not willing to come to the home, this person will go upstairs. Ryan Cheng is the "go upstairs" , "go to the ward" type. Without going upstairs, he could not find the few things he always mentioned to me afterwards. First, there was hardly any food in the LUJIA's house. Second, the house was very cold and had air conditioning, but he could not bear to open it without a water heater. The only source of hot water was a kettle to boil water. Lu Haiyue heard from Ryan Cheng that he would come again the next day. Since the appeal was posted online, Ms. Lu has received numerous phone calls from people advising her to try her luck at a hospital or call a hotline. Few, like Ms. Ryan Cheng, have come straight home.

The next day was February 7th. In the afternoon, Ryan Cheng disinfected the Lu family, comforted the elderly, said: "At home to recuperate well, will go to the hospital. " Then Ryan Cheng went to the community to reflect on the elderly.

All along, the sea month grandma has no strength, the life can not take care of oneself, defecate incontinent. The earliest is Lu Guoxiu new coronary pneumonia symptoms, February 2, Lu Guoxiu to the seventh hospital for examination, home early in the morning, CT showed double lung infection, nucleic acid test results also got February 5, is positive. The fever persisted for several days, and then one of the family members developed symptoms one after the other. After grandma's illness, Lu Haiyue's two aunts would also come to deliver medicine and food, but they had to rely on Lu to take care of their daily lives, worry about their beds and seek help from the outside world. She doesn't have time for tests, and she has two patients in her house, and she can't live without them. However, Lu Haiyue heart know that they are also probably sick, she dizziness, diarrhea, and occasionally the temperature will rise, and the mouth has been dry. Did Not eat the right medicine, did not do the examination, Lu Haiyue is relying on the "own state of mind" , "all the organs are doing the effort" , so hold on.

Lu Haiyue's home

That evening, grandma windowpane oyster got out of bed on her own and sat down on the SPITTOON. The spittoon was uneven, crooked, and the old man fell to the ground. A Wolf Borrow, Lu Haiyue panic in the heart, she tried to put grandma up, with a strong, still can not move. She went to the next room to call his father, the two of them together, still failed. She ran to the community, crying, and asked for help, and talked to the community staff for more than five minutes, and the segment, which was recorded by Lu Haiyue, which she later played for me. I heard two men, one a young girl, panic-stricken, asking for help, the other a middle-aged man, who had heard a request that he did not understand. It didn't end well.

Rejected by the community, Windowpane Oyster ran home again. In the meantime, she made all the emergency calls and made a video call to Ryan Cheng. Camera Toward Grandma, Ryan Cheng let her to test the body temperature, Lu Haiyue reached out to test the back of his hand, forehead, "are ice. ". In the video, Ryan Cheng sees the old man's eyes, and the light in his pupils dissipates. Ryan Cheng finally let Lu Haiyue to press the carotid artery, Lu Haiyue do, "no pulse. " . The mobile phone fell to the ground with a "SPLAT" . If I call again, Lu Haiyue won't answer the phone. It took six or seven minutes to get back on the line.

Luhaiyue later told me that grandma had always been weak and had always given her a feeling of dying. She had a big problem with breathing, so she wasn't allowed to wear a mask because it made it harder to breathe. But she could feel her grandmother wanting to live. "She told me, 'what am I going to do? What am I going to do? If only there were a hospital. ' ". "I couldn't believe the way my grandmother left. I tried her temperature, her pulse, everything, and I kept shaking her, not moving, hitting her, not moving. " I didn't ask any more, and the words went into my mouth without making a sound.

Lu Haiyue was raised by her grandparents. She heard from neighbors that her mother "left her at the door" when she was born. At that time, there was also a pregnant woman living opposite the door. When I opened the door, I saw a baby in front of the door. As soon as grandma saw the baby, she knew who it was. She took the baby home and raised it. For a long time, Lu Guoxiu was not at home either, he was working outside, and windowpane oyster lived with his grandparents. Until five years ago, GRANDPA died, Lu Guoxiu just returned to Wuhan, with an old a small live together. The dog in the kitchen, is GRANDPA died began to raise, "grandma a person afraid of loneliness, dogs with her for so many years. She is most worried about the dog. ". The dog has no name, Lu Haiyue called it "brother" .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As a child, windowpane oyster slept in the same room and bed as her grandmother, head to foot as she grew older. When I was a kid, I started taking insulin for my grandma. Of course, the grandmother is mainly to operate, but the sea moon is responsible for holding a flashlight, hit 12 units in the morning, up to "13" , exhaust, sea moon act as eyes, staring at the numbers on the insulin pen. I had to dip a Q-TIP in alcohol, put pressure on it if there was any bleeding. In order to pay for Windowpane Oyster's school fees, GRANDPA retired to the piano shop to do security, once on the way home car crash, but also quietly back home, legs bloody, sea moon remember. Grandma is also very kind, always take care of the stray dogs downstairs, sometimes go downstairs to feed, really can not go down, take a rope hanging a bowl, loaded with food down the stairs.

The family was particularly troublesome, a trait windowpane oyster inherited. Since the outbreak began in his home, and since he has had symptoms of his own, Windowpane Oyster has visited communities, mostly on the phone, making occasional house calls, and standing in doorways, two meters away from people. It wasn't until things got out of hand that she posted a request for help.

Before that

Ryan Cheng, a native of Wuhan, was born in 1982 to a father in the railway police, and later worked his way into the railway system as a train conductor on bullet trains, while Ryan Cheng followed the railway around many places in the city's nine provinces. But when he was a kid, his dream was to be a COP.

A selfie of volunteer Ryan Cheng

Before his retirement, Ryan Cheng's father had worked in the railway police patrol brigade, and there were many files in the family, anti pickpockets, drug enforcement, everything. Ryan Cheng grew up reading about these cases, and as a child he excelled at detection and counterdetection, with a longing to help the weak and the needy. When he was little, his parents often locked him in the home, the case file inspired him, he found a way, do not open the door without keys, from the seventh floor balcony out, and then returned to the home unscathed. Once in the arcade too excited, forget to go home time, parents came home to find that the doors and windows are good, the child did not, the police, this game of hide and seek to end. Beyond that is Jin Yong, an avid swordsman, with Linghu Chong and Dongfang Bubai as his favorites, the former a maverick and the latter a maverick.

In 1998, at the age of 16, Ryan Cheng enlisted in the Hubei Provincial People's armed police. The next year, Ryan Cheng went with the army to fight the flood, stationed in a county in Songzi, Hubei Province, and lived in a school. One day, Ryan Cheng and his comrades carry a bucket of hot water, shouting "1,2,3, lift" , the comrades lift a number early, open water eyes see to swing out of the bucket, standing next to a child, Ryan Cheng lift the child kicked, a large piece of boiling water in his hands. It's a bad burn. I put on some burn cream. Later in the evening, patrol embankment, two people a group, found "Piping" , emergency rescue, moved a lot of large stones, Burns more fester. This left a lasting legacy for Ryan Cheng, who grabbed a steamed bun from the steamer with his bare hands. Ryan Cheng couldn't resist. He had to pick it up with chopsticks, catch hot water in a Paper Cup. He was afraid to hold the bowl of hot chicken soup. The hand recovered later, still holding a fear of hot things.

After five years in the army, Ryan Cheng missed his chance to become a policeman and retired to the railroad. Until a few years ago, he was still in this aspect of the brain, heard that France has a "Foreign Legion" Armed Forces, allowing foreign nationals to join, after the Legion took over, can work for five years, "criminal record can also erase, get a new identity. ". He studied it online, but decided it was too hard and gave up.

But working on a train can also be an adventure. A regular on the train back from Shenzhen to Wuhan, who gave Ryan Cheng a pack or two of cigarettes from time to time, impressed Ryan Cheng. Once they got to talking, Ryan Cheng took him out of the car and offered him a drink and a song. After three drinks, he borrowed Ryan Cheng's cell phone to make a call and never came back. The phone is a Nokia E71, which has been on the market for a while and is worth a lot of money. Ryan Cheng left a phone from the other side to find clues, pretending to be a girl, plus him Qq, really to find people. At an Internet cafe, Ryan Cheng and several others beat the guy up and marched him into the police station. Ryan Cheng showed me pictures of his youth. He was a good-looking young man. He had been in the army for five years and had good health. He spared no effort in his work.

Now that his city was in danger, Ryan Cheng tried to help. The first is to help people docking a bit of supplies, occasionally a delivery to the hospital, sporadic work. One day in the circle of friends to see the situation of Li Miao, he asked his friends, whether the situation is true. Soon he joined several groups, in the group support, quickly went to the hospital to see Li Miao, a few days earlier than the contact Luhaiyue family.

The volunteers'protective equipment was not up to standard and they had to do their best (pictured on February 7) 

Now that I think about it, Li Miao and the Luhaiyue family are very similar. Li Miao just go to junior high school, with his grandmother. When Ryan Cheng met her, volunteers had already taken her to the hospital, but the beds were tight, and she was in the observation room, inhaling oxygen and wasting time. When he met Ryan Cheng at the hospital downstairs, he was very defensive. His first words were: "If my grandmother doesn't have any, I'll die with her. " Ryan Cheng went to Li's home, the first thing was still sterilization. When the first mop was mopped, it broke. Li Miao found another one. As soon as the mop was mopped, it broke again. Ryan Cheng asked casually, "don't you have a good mop? " The child said, "my grandmother picked up all the MOPS. "

Those words had a big impact on Ryan Cheng. As for Lu Haiyue, the words in Ryan Cheng's mind are "there is only such a big pot in the house that can boil some hot water" and "I haven't had a bath for more than ten days" . The words were so entwined in Ryan Cheng's mind that he did not approve of more rational forms of rescue. He put a lot of emotion into it and tried to do more.

He Calls Li Miaoyuan's birth mother in Sichuan, and finds out why the family has only one child. His mother has her own difficulties, in Sichuan very hard to forget the past, to live their own life. The child grew up without a father, perhaps leading to a growing trust in Ryan Cheng, now in his 20s. Li Miao's phone was posted on the Internet. In the first few days, every two seconds, a phone call came in. Most of them asked what they needed. The child was small and could not tell the difference. He repeated a sentence to countless people, "Don't answer all the phone calls, " Ryan Cheng told him, "your uncle will help you in the future. " Relying on the strength of the Wuhan University, Li's grandmother was hospitalized. Ryan Cheng takes on another role, reasoning with the adolescent Li Miao and persuading the child that his grandmother was now lucky enough not to think about her rebellious ways. Lu Haiyue has been more mature than her peers, Ryan Cheng told her the "loss" of truth, a person living, always experience these, five years ago GRANDPA is once, now is the second time.

Ryan Cheng is one of those characters who "feel better when things are done" and "help others to the end" . Impulsive, had committed suicide when young for love, cut the left hand artery, still scar in the wrist; life has had ups and downs, now belongs to the "fall" period, or else he would not have moved back home to live with his parents; love to make friends, the mantra is "we'll have a drink when the epidemic is over, " and he has said that to me five times since February 7th. He also love Bravado, the heart of the chivalrous dream from time to time, never alone in the event, the community closed, Ryan Cheng in order to go out to help, climbing over the wall during the day, night and then quietly turn back. I thought to myself, if I were to find a match among his favorite Jin Yong characters, it would probably not be some great swordsman, but a character like the seven monsters of the south, whose Kung Fu skills were not so great that it would not prevent them from meddling in the world of martial arts. In his circle of friends, he wrote, what every family lacks is not money, but the last care on earth.

And then..

Back to the night of February 7th. Because the night didn't end with the father and daughter being sent to a hotel.

Lu Haiyue father and daughter in the hotel lobby took a temperature, are normal, the hotel allowed them to stay. Once they were settled, Ryan Cheng breathed a sigh of relief that the long day was over. The other car was gone, and Hwang and I decided to take Ryan Cheng home first. Less than 10 minutes into the drive, Ryan Cheng got another call saying that the CDC would be in the neighborhood in a few minutes to disinfect the victim's home. So we turned around again and went to the hotel to pick up Lu Haiyue.

That night, for the second time, we were in this neighborhood in Zhongnan Subdistrict, Guangzhou. This time, no one went upstairs, except for two CDC staff members and Ms. Lu. I stood four or five meters away from the entrance to the building to watch, see the two of them wearing protective products were rubber texture, more clumsy, and more airtight. Ten minutes later, the sterilizers come downstairs, they can't wait to get out of their gear, and their faces, they look like they're in pain. Another of their colleagues walked over with a pipe, turned around, and saw a large sprayer on his back, much like the pesticide guy. Before you take off your clothes, spill it once, then again after you take it off. I said to Luhaiyue: "You also go over, ask him to sprinkle. "

On the night of February 7th, the CDC was disinfecting its staff.

The CDC didn't like it at first, saying, "this is exciting, " but they still sprayed the landing moon. Ryan Cheng walked over, too, holding out his gloved hands for a high dose of disinfectant. After disinfection, the body still can not be transported. The funeral home can not come until the next day after the death certificate is completed.

So we drove to the hotel a third time. At this time, it was already past midnight. Lao Huang began to interview with two reporters respectively at 9 o'clock in the morning. He had not had a rest for a moment. He was very tired at this time, so he opened four windows wide and let the air in. Cold will lie on the window, ready to burst in. I took off my hat and goggles, want to breathe, only to hear Luhaiyue said: "The dog, I figured it out. "

Luhaiyue promised to take good care of the dog, but as Ryan Cheng said, when, but also manage the dog. "A dog may carry the virus in its hair, and if it is let out, it will cause harm to people. Secondly, it is very good, but also very timid, and will only be bullied by other dogs every time it goes out, " Lu said. Said is thought through, the reason also quite clearly, afterward several times chats with the Lu Haiyue, whenever mentions the dog, she starts to SOB. Later, she stayed in the isolation hotel. At night, when she heard the dog barking, her heart ached and she told herself that she had no choice. Then I went to the shelter hospital, and I slept with it in my head. Leaving home for the last time, Luhaiyue put a bucket of dog food on the table, later regret, worried about the high position, "I hope his desire to survive, can force it down to eat dog food. ". It's sad to see a dog given up too soon for not being a priority.

On Feb. 8, Ryan Cheng's decision to send Ms. Lu to a hotel had consequences. The foundation that funded him did not recognise Ryan Cheng's approach and decided not to work with him any more, so he went back to working alone. The hotel room where Luhaiyue stayed with her father was sealed off by the police when they heard the news. Father and daughter have nowhere to go again. Lu Haiyue and her father went to a hotel, apparently bringing the risk of infection here. I asked Ryan Cheng what he thought. Ryan Cheng said the night was a "dilemma, " but he could not let the father and daughter go home. The best way, of course, is to find an empty house, but where is such an ideal house. As for the risks and pitfalls, Ryan Cheng knew better than to act on them.

But for Luhaiyue, the night in the hotel, finally took a hot bath, this is the first time in more than 10 days. One day, it all happened so fast and so fast. Not until lying down, Lu Haiyue realized that his father was also very sad. He was in another bed not far away, with his back to himself, crying, but did not want her to find out.

Later, Lu Haiyue went into the shelter, wearing clothes that Ryan Cheng had given him.

February 8th was also a day of great events. Her father got into the shelter and walked to Wuchang's shelter hospital that afternoon. Leaving Lu Haiyue a person, is also a do not know where to stay the night. Ryan Cheng Thought of Miao Li. Li Miao's grandmother had been admitted to the hospital, and he was willing to take in the homeless sister for one night. "We are both unhappy -- to the sky's end. I heard Lu Haiyue mentioned Li Miao, said is "brother" , "with his brother added Wechat" , "slowly also know the situation of his brother.

I asked Lu and Ryan Cheng what they wanted to do when the epidemic was over. Ryan Cheng's answer was two words: "Make Money. " . He is 38, unmarried, has a girlfriend of six years and has plenty of life plans to make. But for now, Ryan Cheng is still helping out in Wuhan. On Feb. 23, after a few days on his own, he began working as a security guard at a nursing home and asked me "can I get an N95 mask? ". Lu Haiyue was only 24 years old. After wandering around the city for a few days, she finally found some stability in the shelter hospital. Still thinking about grandma, still worried about the dog. But there are very gentle sister nurses, every day good food, milk and fruit, and sometimes at night there is a midnight snack. She says she wants to get rid of her lazy ways and find a steady job and a life with her father when the epidemic is over.

(all of the interviewees except Ryan Cheng are assumed names)
